fields: I should be helping with breakfast.
You were up late again, weren't you?
Don't be silly. That's no excuse.
Let me take care of it, Senpai.
If you leave the storehouse in this state,  Fujimura-sensei will scold you.
Guess I'll take you up on that offer, then.
Great. I'll be waiting for you, Senpai.
Falling asleep before finishing shows that I lack focus.
I feel terrible making you do all this, Sakura.
I do it because I want to.
Other sauces don't belong on rice with grated yams!  Especially not oyster sauce!
I switched the labels on the bottles earlier! Gotcha good, huh?
Who pulls a stunt like that first thing in the morning?
You're turning twenty-five this year, for heaven's sake.
Guess you'll always be the same old Fuji-nee.
I thought you seemed awfully quiet.
You've been planning this ever since then?
I spent a whole lot of time that I should have spent grading tests.
So I gotta run, or I'll never get them done in time!
Don't go back to sleep and wind up late, okay?
Your cooking was as delicious as ever, Sakura-chan!
Does being the landlord's daughter  give her the right to eat here every day?
She's no better than a freeloader.
Did you do something to upset her yesterday?
I accidentally called her by that one nickname.
You know she hates it when you call her that.
In our next story, workers in a Shinto business district  office building were hospitalized
after passing out late last night.
Hear that? Another gas leak in Shinto.
That's messed up. We need to be careful too.
I always double-check the gas valve, so we'll be fine.
Well, work hard at club practice.
Maybe you could stop by the dojo?
I have to go to the student council office this morning.
Look forward to dinner tonight, okay?
The school's budgetary allocations are completely unbalanced.
Yeah, athletic clubs get the lion's share of the budget, and the rest get the crumbs.
As a result, the facilities available to non-athletic clubs are in disrepair.
They've given zero thought to resolving our heater issues.
You mean this isn't the only broken one?
As I thought, it's just showing its age.
It won't take long, so could you wait outside?
Of course. I'll get out of your way.
There are two spots where the heating element is about to break.
The heat transfer pipes should be good for a while.
I can patch the power cord with electrical tape for now.
Well, if it isn't the student council president.
Already up and patrolling the school?
Or are you doing maintenance on the club rooms?
Either way, I see you're as diligent as always.
And what are you up to this morning?
Why are you here so early when you aren't in any clubs?
I asked you for help, but you ended up doing all the work. My bad, Emiya.
Where's the next one? We don't have all day.
They said it had been acting up for a while,  and now it looks like it's reached the end of its lifespan.
If it's dead, I can't fix that.
You're better off buying a new one.
While that's true, I'd appreciate it if you could take a look at it anyway.
It looked dead to me, but you might be able to tell if it's just pretending.
Okay. I'll give it a shot.
The art club's heater will have to wait until lunchtime.
You're quite the busy bee this morning, Emiya.
I was wondering what you'd been up to after quitting the club.
You're the student council president's errand boy, eh?
If you need anything on your end, just let me know, Shinji.
If it's something I can help with, I will.
Maintaining bows was never your strong suit, after all.
You're not part of the club anymore,  so don't show your face near the dojo again!
Is he serious? Did he forget that he was the one  who drove you out in the first place?
It's okay. That's just how he is.
You get used to it eventually.
Uh-oh. Fujimura-sensei is about to come barreling in.
Good morning, class! I'll take attendance now.
Emiya, if you don't eat your lunch soon, you won't get to.
The heaters are one thing, but you didn't have to agree to fix personal items too.
Don't worry about it. Like they say, in for a penny, in for a pound.
There's such a thing as being too considerate.
Being helpful is all well and good,  but you should really learn to say no.
You take "turn no one away" too far, Emiya.
Do I seem like that much of a pushover?
You're leaving yourself open to being  taken advantage of by the unscrupulous.
Surely you could turn people down every once in a while.
What're you talking about? Helping others is a good deed.
That's not something the heir to a temple should be complaining about.
I'm just saying that you take it too far, Emiya.
If you keep going like this, you'll burn out.
If you don't summon yours soon, you'll die, Onii-chan.
Of all the times to come home late!
I said in homeroom that it hasn't  been safe in town lately, remember?
Do you get that from Kiritsugu-san?
I worry about what'll happen to you if you keep spending all your time trying to help people.
Has Senpai always been this way?
Yeah, for as long as I've known him.
Shirou just doesn't have it in him to ignore people in need.
Comfort the afflicted, and afflict the comfortable, you know?
When he was a kid, he wrote in an essay,  "When I grow up, I wanna be a champion of justice!"
Wow, he must have been adorable.
And whose fault do you think that is?
When kids grow up around immature adults,  they get funny ideas in their heads.
If you don't like it, cook your own damn food for once.
You're going to make me cry!
I can't believe that I still can't do something this basic.
I'm gonna be a novice forever.
How do I become a champion of justice?
What's he thinking, raising his hand against his little sister?
I, um, got this when I tripped and fell.
You can't get a bruise like that from tripping.
My brother had nothing to do with this, I swear!
I got hurt by myself. That's all.
Well, if you say so. I'll leave it at that.
Thank you. And I'm sorry, Senpai.
Why are you apologizing? It's Shinji who's to blame.
Do I smell your famous rolled omelets, Shirou?
Sorry, Issei. I'm going to eat in the cafeteria today.
Going with the chef's special for lunch today, are we?
Not eating with the prez today?
Has Sakura seemed okay to you lately?
Sakura? Yeah, she's practicing her heart out.
It's her brother that's the problem.
He's been taking his frustrations out on the first-year boys.
From what I hear, he got shot down pretty hard by Tohsaka.
Anyway, Shinji's been in a foul mood ever since yesterday.
I've had to keep an eye on him all through practice, so I'm exhausted.
Yeah, Shinji does have a nasty temper.
I feel like he might be planning to get even with Tohsaka somehow.
Nah, not even Shinji would go anywhere near someone who'd rejected him.
But he can't avoid her if she comes to him.
I'm not sure why, but Tohsaka's been  coming to watch at the dojo a lot lately.
I guess you didn't know, since you quit and all.
But man, the look on his face was hilarious!
When Shinji gets mad, he stays that way.
I hate to break it to you, Matou Shinji, but Tohsaka Rin isn't gonna turn up, no matter how long you wait!
Maki, this guy doesn't match the description Lady Mitsuzuri gave.
He doesn't have wavy hair, for one.
Oh yeah? I bet he just slicked it back with a little water!
A face this stupid-looking could only belong to Matou Shinji!
See what I mean? That's what the culprit always says.
Sorry, but would you mind showing us your student ID?
The guy who fixes our gear whenever he has a spare moment?
I've never heard that nickname before,  but I do know the track and field captain.
Sorry. It seemed like you were looking for someone, so we just assumed.
That's okay. What was that about Tohsaka not coming?
Yeah. Tohsaka's taking the day off with a cold, good sir.
It's hard to believe that a flawless model student like her could even get sick, though, right?
We're sorry for the trouble our circus attraction here caused you, Emiya.
But you shouldn't be here, either.
Weren't you told that students with no  club activities should go straight home?
There was a homicide by the intersection near school.
A family of four was attacked,  and only the youngest child survived.
The parents and older sister were stabbed to death.
The killer is still at large, and the nature of the killings has sparked considerable unrest.
In Shinto, they've got those gas leaks, while over here, we've got these gruesome murders.
It's only natural they'd be sending students home early.
Helping others and being a champion of justice aren't the same thing.
I'll get straight to the point. Would you rather be sent off to an orphanage,  or taken in by a man you just met?
Then let's get you dressed right away.
You should get acclimated to your new home as soon as possible.
Oh, I forgot to mention something.
It's important that you know this, all right?
Well... For starters, I'm a magician.
I've still got some time before work.
You're alive... You're alive! You're alive!
I'm so glad I found someone.
By saving even one person, I've saved myself.
All I remember of that day ten years ago  is that it was hot, that I couldn't breathe, and that many others tried to save people, only to die in the process.
It makes me angry to see people die after trying so hard.
Is it greedy of me to wish for a happy ending, full of smiles for all?
Because that would involve saving  everyone without exception, Shirou.
Kiritsugu's answer never really convinced my younger self.
After all, I knew he was an all-powerful magician who had saved my life.
So I asked Kiritsugu if he could have  saved everyone back then.
Shirou. Saving one person means not saving another.
You see, a person can only save those  who are on the side they've chosen to take.
It should be obvious, right? I mean, that's the very definition of a champion of justice.
Salvation shouldn't apply to a limited number of people.
I can't bear the thought of more strangers dying around me like they did that day.
If it's ramen you want, you've come to the right person! Really, now?
I happen to be an expert on ramen!
Why'd you send her home by herself?
Weren't you saying it wasn't safe to go out alone at night?
It's fine, it's fine. I sent one of my men with her.
You should've gone yourself. You're our teacher, after all.
If I did that, I wouldn't get to eat dinner until after ten!
It's your fault for staying out so late at your job, anyway!
I always have to sit here starving whenever you have work.
If you're so hungry, why can't you just get dinner at your own house?
Oh, someone gave that to me,  but I don't want it, so you can have it!
But I don't want it either!
You're sadly mistaken if you think  you can hit me with skills like yours.
If you don't like it, I suggest you practice some more.
But more importantly, Shirou, I'm famished!
I've been waiting for ages, so hurry up and make dinner!
Senpai, I won't be able to help with  the cooking for a while starting tonight.
Don't worry about it. It's the weekend, after all.
I'm sure you have people to hang out with.
It's really just a personal thing,  and I'll still be going to club practices, so if anything comes up, please come to the dojo, and I'll see what I can do!
I wouldn't go out and have fun just because it's the weekend!
So... I'd appreciate it if you didn't get the wrong idea.
If something comes up, I'll stop by the dojo.
Did I cut myself while I was tinkering with some old junk?
It doesn't hurt or anything, so it should fade soon.
I'm fine. Nothing to worry about.
With your efforts, it looks like we'll have all the equipment fixed before exams begin.
Thank you again for your help.
I need to talk to you. Come with me for a minute.
As you can see, I don't have a minute to spare.
Whatever your little problem is, it can wait. Isn't that right, girls?
Hang on, Shinji. This is about the bruise on Sakura's wrist.
Don't dodge the question. You hurt her again, didn't you?
I don't know what you're talking about, and I don't care.
Look, Emiya. You're starting to get on my nerves.
Yeah, we're brother and sister, so that's all the more reason to mind your own business, isn't it?
You really don't know how she got it?
Or did Sakura tell you that I beat her?
It's not nice to make baseless accusations, Emiya.
I suppose. I'm sorry I suspected you.
If you're sorry, prove it by doing me a favor.
See, the dojo's in kind of a mess right now.
If you've got time to play the concerned citizen,  maybe you could do something about it, Emiya-kun?
Didn't Fujimura-sensei tell you to clean it up, Senpai?
I mean, if I start cleaning now,  the shop will be closed by the time I finish.
Take it from here, will you?
We'll leave it to you, then.
Today just wasn't your lucky day, boy.
Now that you're a witness, I can't let you live.
Dead men tell no tales, and all that.
Curse with your dying breath that you were born with no luck and no power.
You've given me some dirty work.
How can I call myself a hero after this?
I got a good look at the girl's Servant.
I'll be a good boy and return.
Jeez. My Master's a real nasty piece of work.
He's not going to make it. Not with a skewered heart.
Don't do this to me... Why did it have to be you?
Why did you have to pick this hour, on this day, to be here?
The man in blue and the man in red...
They were far beyond ordinary humans.
So I really was almost killed.
I was saved by someone who came along afterward.
I wish I could at least thank them.
And here I was trying to be considerate.  I figured it'd hurt less if you never saw it coming.
Can't believe I got stuck with killing the same person twice in one day.
I guess the world's a bloody place, no matter what the era.
Make sure you go into the light this time, boy.
It's faint, but I sense mana.
So that's why you're still alive after  taking my spear through your heart.
This might be fun after all.
I gave you a chance, but you went and wasted it.
If you're a man, show some dignity.
Checkmate. That last move was pretty surprising, boy.
You think fast on your feet, but you're hopeless at magic.
You seem to have potential, though.
Maybe you were meant to be the seventh.
Well, even if you were, this is the end for you.
My life was saved, so I'm not going to give it up so easily!
I need to live. I have to fulfill my duty.
And I can't do that if I'm dead!
I'm not gonna die for no reason in a place like this, killed by a guy like you
who takes lives like it's nothing!
I, the Saber-class Servant, have come in response to your summons.
Henceforth, you hold my sword in your hands, and I hold your fate in mine.
Why do you conceal your own weapon?!
What's the matter, Lancer?  No self-respecting spearman stays rooted to the spot.
If you will not come to me, I shall come to you!
Before that, let me ask you one thing.
Your Noble Phantasm: is it a sword?
It may be a battle axe. Or perhaps it is a spear.
Or it might even be a bow, Lancer.
Since this is our first meeting, would you be interested in calling it a draw?
A shame. I was only ordered to observe.
So you escaped my mightiest blow, Saber.
No, an attack that reverses cause and effect?
Gae Bolg... You are Ireland's Child of Light!
If I use that move, it has to kill.
My lord is a coward, you see.
You dodged my spear, so he's ordering me home.
You're more than welcome to follow me.
But if you do, be prepared to die!
As you can see, I am a Saber-class Servant.
No, that's not right. That isn't what I want to ask you.
You're not a legitimate Master, are you?
Hang on. Isn't it kinda weird to start calling me "Master" out of the blue?
Yes. I much prefer the way that sounds.
Do try to avoid using them carelessly.
Shirou, my wounds, if you please.
Sorry, but complicated magic like that is beyond me.
I shall face them in my current condition, then.
One more battle should not pose a problem.
I could have defeated them handily, and you ordered me to stop!
I have no idea what's going on.
If I'm your Master, at least fill me in!
You would demand such a thing with the enemy before us?!
Ah, so that's how it is, my good novice Master?
I have no reason to fight.
He's a certified phony, that priest.
Will you participate in the Holy Grail War?
Not really. I can't do anything like this. What do you mean, you can't?
Working with glass is the most basic of the basics.
I don't know any of these "basics" or "fundamentals."
Honestly, how did someone like you manage to summon Saber?
First things first, I need to repay you for earlier.
To be blunt, you've been chosen as a Master.
Have you noticed a brand somewhere on your body?
She is referring to the Command Spells, Shirou.
Yes. Those symbolize your status as a Master.
They're also spells which bind your Servant.
So as long as you have those, you can control your Servant.
What do you mean, as long as I have them?
They force your Servant's obedience,  even if it means bending them to your will.
Saber broke off her attack earlier, remember?
However, you only get three such orders, so try not to waste them.
If you use them all, you'll probably be killed, so I suggest you exercise caution.
The Holy Grail War is based around Masters defeating other Masters.
Whichever Master prevails over the other six  will win the Holy Grail, which can grant any wish.
Hey, hold on a second. What do you mean by "Holy Grail"?
To cut a long story short, you've been dragged into a ritual.
One called the Holy Grail War, fought by seven Masters
a battle to the death between mages.
What the hell are you talking about?
I'm simply laying out the facts.
Besides, it should be obvious even to you at this point.
After all, a Servant nearly killed you not once but twice.
I was also chosen as a Master.
Think of your Servant as a familiar, granted to you by the Grail to help you win the Holy Grail War.
She doesn't look much like a familiar to me.
Though they're technically classed as familiars, Servants are actually superhuman beingsheroes from the past.
Heroes from the past? Saber too?
Servants are heroes summoned from legends
be they ancient or moderninto our time and given physical forms.
It's the Master's role to summon them, upon which they are made manifest through a phenomenon of the Grail.
Basically, a Servant is always with you in spirit form.
And should the need arise, you can  make them materialize and fight.
So that guy in red can transform at will between spirit and physical form?
I'm having him keep watch outside for the time being.
Do you understand everything so far?
If you want a more detailed explanation,  you should talk to the man who oversees the Grail War.
is that you have no choice but to fight, and that Servants are powerful familiars,  so you should use yours well.
Now, then. From what Emiya-kun has said, I gather that you're in an incomplete state, Saber?
Yes. As you say, I am not at full fighting strength.
Shirou is not a full-fledged Master, so even replenishing my mana is likely to be difficult.
Hey, what are you two talking about, Tohsaka?
Servants maintain their existence here with mana supplied by their Masters.
But because you're a novice, she can't get mana from you directly, which will make things difficult.
I have to admit, I didn't expect you to be so forthcoming with me.
You'd already realized something was wrong, so there was no point in concealing it.
Given that, I felt revealing our hand to an enemy such as yourself
could help Shirou better understand our situation.
Damn it, that makes it even more of a waste!
If I were Saber's Master, this war would be as good as won!
Hey, are you saying I'm not worthy of her?
Of course I am, you hack!
To see the man who knows all about the Holy Grail War.
You want to know what all this is for, don't you?
Of course. It's kind of late, though.
Well, it's your call. What about you, Saber?
Oh, so you do think like a Master.
You don't want me talking to Saber?
Damn, I'm starting to feel like something is wrong with her.
I mean, Saber's a hero from the past, right?
She won't be able to make sense of the modern world.
Servants adapt to whatever era they find themselves in.
As such, I am quite familiar with this time.
This is also not the first time I have been summoned to this era.
No way! What are the odds?
Why do you suppose Saber won't come in with us?
She said she's been in this time period before.
So maybe something happened  between her and the phony priest here.
Tohsaka, what kind of guy is this priest?
He used to be my father's pupil.
After Father died, he became my guardian.
He and Father taught me everything I know.
Wait, so this priest is also a mage?
That's right. He's a certified phony, that priest.
You've accepted none of my prior invitations, but here you are now with an unusual guest.
I take it this means he is the seventh, Rin?
What is your name, seventh Master?
Then, Emiya Shirou, can I assume you are the Master of the Saber-class Servant?
Yeah, I made a contract with Saber, but this stuff about Masters and the Holy Grail War is all nonsense to me.
If a Master is supposed to be a proper mage, you really ought to pick someone else.
I see. This is serious indeed.
You'll need to start from square one with him.
This is the first time you have ever sought my assistance.
Emiya Shirou, the status of Master cannot be yielded to another.
And, once conferred, it is not a thing  from which one can simply walk away.
Being a Master is a trial you have been chosen to undergo.
You will not be freed from that ordeal until you win the Grail.
Emiya Shirou, this battle you've found yourself caught up in is called the Holy Grail War.
Some nonsense about seven Masters fighting to the death, right?
It is a ritual meant to select the one who is worthy to hold the Grail.
You keep talking about this "Holy Grail",  but you don't mean the actual Holy Grail, do you?
The Grail that appears in this town is the genuine article.
For proof, one need look no further than the unrivaled miracle of the Servants.
A Holy Grail capable of this can surely grant its holder limitless power.
In the face of such a fact, the item's "authenticity" is irrelevant.
Then why force people to go through this Holy Grail War thing?
If it's that powerful, why not just share it?
A reasonable suggestion, but only one may claim the Grail.
We did not make that decision. Rather, the Grail itself decided it.
This is all the work of the Grail itself.
It selects its one true owner by having the Masters fight to win it.
That is the Holy Grail War.
Even if only one can be chosen, I don't like the idea that that person has to kill the other Masters.
We don't have to kill each other, Emiya-kun.
No, it is a fight to the death.
Listen, the Holy Grail that appears in this city is a spiritual object.
And since it's spiritual, we can't touch it.
Do you see where I'm going?
The point of the Holy Grail War is to  get rid of all the other Masters' Servants.
Which means that there is no rule stating that you have to kill the other Masters.
Emiya Shirou, if I may ask...
Do you think that you could defeat your own Servant?
Servants are difficult to defeat, even if you have a Servant yourself.
So what to do? The answer is simple, is it not?
No matter how powerful the Servant, if its Master is killed, the Servant will vanish.
Killing the Master is the quickest way.
But what about the opposite case?  What if a Master's Servant is destroyed first?
Only Servants can touch the Grail, right?
That implies that a Master who's lost their Servant no longer has any value.
No, as long as their Command Spells exist,  so do their rights as a Master.
So, if there were a Servant that had lost its Master and had nowhere to go, it would still have a chance to rejoin the battle.
It is for that reason that Masters kill other Masters.
Then what if I used up all my Command Spells right now?
True, you would relinquish your rights as a Master.
Although I cannot imagine a mage using magic as powerful as a Command Spell in so wasteful a manner.
Any such mage could not even be called incompetent
they would be no more than a coward.
Then let us go back to the beginning, Emiya Shirou.
If you wish to forfeit your status as Master, then so be it.
Simply use up your Command Spells and break your contract with Saber.
If you do so, I shall guarantee your safety until the Holy Grail War's end.
Why would I need you to guarantee my safety?
I was dispatched here to oversee the cycle of Holy Grail Wars.
Safeguarding mages that are no longer Masters is the overseer's top priority.
The Holy Grail War didn't begin just now?
This is the fifth such war.
The previous one was ten years ago, making this the shortest cycle yet.
This has happened four times before?
With each cycle, the Holy Grail War has only grown more brutal.
Driven by their desires, Masters have engaged in indiscriminate slaughter.
Then what would happen if the Grail fell into evil hands?
It is beyond our means to stop one whom the Grail has chosen.
After all, it is an omnipotent, wish-granting chalice.
If you do not wish that to happen, Emiya Shirou, win it yourself.
At the very least, if you win, it will not go to an indiscriminate killer, yes?
I have no reason to fight.
So you have no interest in what the Grail's holder does, no matter what atrocities may be wrought?
If you have no reason to fight, so be it.
I take it the events of ten years ago do not concern you?
At the end of the previous Grail War,  an unworthy Master touched the Grail.
I know not of what that Master wished.
All we know is the resultant disaster.
The Shinto fire, whose cause remains officially unknown, was the result of the last Holy Grail War.
You said that this is the fifth one, right?
Has anyone ever won the Grail, then?
One man did indeed hold the Grail, albeit briefly.
That Grail did not achieve completion.
The result of a foolish man letting sentiment get the better of him.
Simply causing the Grail to appear is trivial.
Once the seven Servants are gathered, the Grail will appear in time.
As Rin says, it is not necessary to slay the other Masters.
But unless you do so, the Grail will never be complete.
It chooses the Master who is worthy of it.
That is why this man, who avoided fighting, did not win the Grail.
In other words, obtaining the Grail is meaningless unless you settle things with the other Masters first.
In the last war, the Master who was first to get his hands on the Grail was a nave fool.
That is all I have to say.
Will you participate in the Holy Grail War?
Rejoice, boy. Your wish will finally come true.
Your wish cannot come true without a clear and distinct evil.
Though you may refuse to admit it, a champion of justice
must have an evil to defeat.
Shirou, have you concluded your business here?
I have decided to fight as a Master.
Will you agree to me as your Master, Saber?
You have been my Master from the very start.
Did I not swear that my body would be your blade?
I'll be counting on you, Saber.
What? We aren't supposed to shake hands?
I was simply taken by surprise.
Allow me to renew my vow.
So long as the Command Spells are on your body, I shall serve as your blade.
If the Holy Grail War was the cause of the fire ten years ago, I won't let something like that ever happen again.
No offense, but you should go home on your own.
I brought you here because you weren't officially my enemy yet.
But now, you're a fellow Master, Emiya-kun.
I have no intention of fighting you, Tohsaka.
Jeez, why did I even bother bringing you here?
If an easily slain enemy presents itself, we'd be remiss not to take advantage.
You don't have to tell me that.
Will you take pity on that boy again?
Don't tell me you have feel
And I can't fight with a clear conscience until I've repaid him.
In that case, send for me when you have repaid this debt of yours.
Regardless of why you did it,  you used a Command Spell to stop Saber.
So I have to go easy on you to balance the scales.
You get hung up on the weirdest things, Tohsaka.
I know that. But I have no choice.
I hate being indebted to someone.
You're a good person, aren't you?
Flattery won't make me go any easier on you!
I know. But I don't want us to be enemies if I can help it.
Don't you get that you're just in the way?
Didn't we just decide that we would fight together?!
A disgraceful hind deserves to be skewered.
This is the second time we've met like this.
It's nice to meet you too, Rin.
